properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 20 at 4:09AM AKST until February 21 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow occurring. Visibility one half mile
or less at times. Less than 1 inch of additional snow
accumulation expected. Travel will be difficult.

* WHERE...Yukon Delta.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM Friday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds gusting to 40 mph will cause low
visibility in blowing snow. Significant drifting snow will
occur. The worst conditions are along the coast, with less
severe conditions inland.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow and blowing snow means periods
of snow and blowing snow will cause travel difficulties.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST FRIDAY
